rom the early twentieth century to the present. It shows that the current revolution is best understood as the coming together of two older ways of knowing—collecting and experimenting, the museum and the laboratory. Ultimately, Bruno J. Strasser argues that by serving as knowledge repositories, as well as indispensable tools for producing new knowledge, these databases function as digital museums for the twenty-first century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aBig data. 0aBiological modelsxData processing. 0aBiological specimensxCollection and preservationxTechnological innovations. 0aBiology, ExperimentalxData processing. 0aBiology, ExperimentalxDatabases. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  abig data.  acollection.  adatabase.  ahistory.  alaboratory.  amuseum.  anatural history.  aopen access.  apublic participation.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2019 Englishz978311061053608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2019z9783110606386oZDB-23-DPM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311071194340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226635187423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226635187.jpg  a978-3-11-061053-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-071194-3  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2019  aZDB-23-DPMb2019